    <!-- ═══ FAQ ═══ -->
    <section class="px-section">
      <div class="px-container">
        <div class="px-sec-head center px-reveal">
          <h2>Questions, answered.</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="px-faq px-reveal">
          <details>
            <summary>What makes Aqua different from a chatbot?</summary>
            <p>Chatbots answer. Aqua plans, verifies, and executes. Each request runs through a planning layer, a reasoning check, and an execution engine that produces real artifacts — code, documents, and deployed projects in your workspace.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>How does the credit system work?</summary>
            <p>You get free credits every day, reset at midnight. When you need more, buy a prepaid pack — purchased credits never expire and there are no recurring charges.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Does Aqua remember my previous work?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Aqua maintains persistent memory tied to your account — your projects, preferences, and context carry across conversations and sessions.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Can I upload my existing codebase or documents?</summary>
            <p>Yes. Upload archives, PDFs, Word documents, spreadsheets, and presentations. Aqua ingests and reasons over them, and can propose precise, reviewable edits to your code.</p>
          </details>
          <details>
            <summary>Which AI models power Aqua?</summary>
            <p>Aqua routes each request to the model best suited to the task, with automatic provider fallback for reliability. You work with one interface; the routing is handled for you.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

